#. type: Title ###
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:322
#, no-wrap
msgid "A Life On Our Planet by David Attenborough."
msgstr "Uma Vida No Nosso Planeta de David Attenborough."

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:325
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/9137c033-8ca1-41e9-af61-0ebe6fe985fc.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/9137c033-8ca1-41e9-af61-0ebe6fe985fc.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:327
msgid ""
"A Life on Our Planet, the companion book to the documentary of the same "
"name, is half Attenborough’s personal experience as a witness of decades of "
"environmental disaster, half his recommendations for healing and rewilding "
"the planet. It’s an inspiring plea for change from one of the most respected "
"environmental educators around - a plea by one of the world’s most beloved "
"humans for the imperiled planet he so clearly loves."
msgstr ""
"Uma Vida no Nosso Planeta, o livro que acompanha o documentário com o mesmo "
"nome, é metade sobre a experiência pessoal de Attenborough como uma "
"testemunha de décadas de desastres ambientais, metade sobre as suas "
"recomendações para curar e repopularr de vida selvagem o planeta. É um apelo "
"inspirador por mudança de um dos educadores ambientais mais respeitados de "
"sempre - um apelo de um dos humanos mais amado do mundo pelo planeta em "
"perigo que ele tanto adora."

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:329
msgid "Here are a few other books recommended by readers..."
msgstr "Aqui tens mais uns livros recomendados pelos leitores..."

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "**The Overstory by Richard Powers.**\n"
msgstr "**A Árvore-Mundo de Richard Powers.**\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:333
msgid ""
"A brilliant novel exploring the lives of people transformed, in one way or "
"another, by trees. Though fiction, it’s meticulously researched - the "
"politics, activism, and science are all real."
msgstr ""
"Um romance brilhante que explora a forma como a vida de algumas pessoas "
"transformada, de uma forma ou outra, pelas árvores. Apesar de ser ficção, é "
"pesquisado meticulosamente - a política, ativismo, e ciência são todos reais."

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:335
msgid "\"My favourite read in a very long time\" (Sarah)"
msgstr "\"A minha leitura preferida desde há muito tempo\" (Sarah)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:338
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Braiding Sweetgrass: Indigenous Wisdom, Scientific Knowledge and the Teachings of Plants by Robin Wall Kimmerer.**\\\n"
"A lovely memoir exploring the author’s use of both science and her Potawatomie cultural heritage to understand plants. \"It’s bloody awesome!\" (Nick)\n"
msgstr ""
"**Entrançando Glyceria: Sabedoria Indígena, Conhecimento Científico e Ensinamentos das Plantas por Robin Wall Kimmerer.**\\\n"
"Uma memória encantadora que explora quer o uso da ciência da autora quer a sua herança cultural Potawatomie para compreender as plantas. \"É absolutamente incrível!\" (Nick)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-02-09-global-newsletter-48.md:340
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Our House Is On Fire: Greta Thunberg’s Call to Save the Planet by Jeanette Winter.**\\\n"
"A children’s picture-book about Greta Thunberg and her powerful message. Adults can read it, too, of course. \"Very moving, not only about the climate crisis, but also about a family which struggles everyday to help their children come to terms with a world with insane values\" (David)  \n"
msgstr ""
